SIMPLE: outstanding
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outstanding
<hw>Out*stand"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That stands out;
undischarged; uncollected; not paid; <as>as, <ex>outstanding</ex>
obligations</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Revenues . . . as well <qex>outstanding</qex> as collected.</q>
<rj><qau>A. Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Conspicuously excellent; markedly superior;
distinguished.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>So prominent so as to attract notice; conspicuous;
usually but not always in a good sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outstare</ent>⟦br⟧
